replies.author: Manish Yadav
replies.text: @Kabiraj Pudasaini brother your translation of what he said is actually misleading because you just focused on that particular sentence which does not exactly point out about the separation of Madhesh ( Terai). From the beginning of the interview he has been focusing on places he went from Mechi to Mahakali where he found marginalized groups living under poverty without any basic facilities. He was not even talking about his own village to gain that empathy which most of our political leaders do. At those places people came to him for help and he felt that the people were under represented in those areas, their voices were not heard and they were living in poor conditions. He said he started his political career with an agenda of separating Madhesh from Nepal but as time passed his agendas transformed according to the time and the situation. His agendas were more focused towards the development of Madhesh and representation of the Madhesi people in each every government body of Nepal. So Kabiraj Pudasaini brother try to analayze stuffs as a whole and see the co-relation before jumpng into conclusion from one single sentence. Thank you.
